"For this shot, I've placed my #Elinchrom Rotalux Deep Octa Softbox 100cm (39″) directly across from the direction my model is facing and slightly behind her. There's enough light spilling onto her so that her face is properly exposed, but the shadows on her cheek, nose, and around her eye help to sculpt her face and create a more intense mood."

Find out why the Rotalux Deep Octa Softbox 100cm (39″) is one of @_emilyteague’s favorite light shapers and how this modifier enables her to produce diverse lighting atmospheres during her various photo sessions.

ONE WORKSHOP SEAT LEFT! 🎉 

One of our four workshop attendees for October 9th had to pull out which means we’ve now got one seat left for that day! Thanks to inquiries that couldn’t make the 9th, we’ve also opened a second workshop day happening Dec 1st. We would love to see you at either! 

@brandinicolephoto and I will be covering everything from providing portfolio overviews, concepting, color theory, moodboading, team building, production tips, and several lighting set ups with both constant and flash. 

Attendees will get individual time to shoot each look with our lovely model & friend  @reilly.hail. We’ll also be working with our wildly talented hair & makeup artist @aliciadangelo. And we’ll be photographing you too! Each attendee will receive a portrait taken by us. 

To finish things off before we all head to dinner- we’ll be giving out email templates for client outreach & team communication- plus a few special surprises that we hope will delight you. 

We are here to help at any level you’re at and looking forward to curating information to help fit your needs & goals. Hope to see you there! 

Book your spot at brandiandemily.com

New Delhi, India // 2018

Prior to moving to New York City in 2019, I spent about 5 years constantly on the move. The longest I stayed in one place was between 3 to 6 months before the urge to escape took over again. I would travel until I ran out of money, return home and work as much as possible, then escape again. I traveled on my own to about 30 countries throughout North America, Europe, Asia, the Middle East, the Caribbean, and Africa. With my camera as my companion and guiding my direction, I felt a sense of purpose wherever I went. 

I finally set down roots in a home and city that I’m profoundly grateful to call mine. I feel so much more content & stable than I did during those days constantly running around- but God do I miss the unknown paths, navigating and solving daily challenges, and these beautiful, brief moments of connection.
